staffs.bio: Originally from Ottawa, Ontario Chelsea admires the abundance of activities and natural beauty of the West. Chelsea began her West Coast journey in Pender Island, working at a resort spa

staffs.name: Elijah
staffs.bio: Back home in Ontario, Jen decided she wanted to become a massage therapist shortly after finishing her Bachelor of Kinesiology at university which she had started for her love and interest in anatomy and physiology.

staffs.name: Charlotte
staffs.bio: Natalie was born and raised in Hertford, England, and has been skiing from a tiny 18 months old. Ski instructing brought her to Whistler in 2008 and she has been calling Canada home ever since.

staffs.name: Logan
staffs.bio: From a little town called Provence in the beautiful South of France to Whistler in 2017, Nathalie has come a long way to share her 6 years of beauty therapist experience with her guests at the Whistler Day Spa. She loves the title Beauty therapist as she believes visiting a beautician IS a type of therapy,
